      • exec

        public Project exec(TerminalScanner scan,
                    DataModel model,
                    User user)
             throws PermissionException,
                    CancelException,
                    java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Execute the create project scenario.


        0. Ask user to create a new or clone a project.
        a) Create new
        a1. Ask user the name of the project
        a2. Ask user the description of the project
        a3. Ask user the starting date of the project
        a4. Ask user the budget estimate of the project.
        a5. Ask user the lead developer by providing a list of possibilities.
        a6. Show the user the details of the created project.
        b) Clone project (without BugReports)
        b1. Ask user which project by providing a list of possibilities.
        b2. Ask user the version number
        b3. Ask user the starting date
        b4. Ask user the budget estimate
        b5. Go to step a5

        Specified by:
        exec in interface Cmd<Project>
        Parameters:
        scan - The Scanner trough which to ask the questions.
        model - The model to use to access the model.
        user - The user who wants to execute this Cmd.
        Returns:
        The user chosen by the person to login as.
        Throws:
        PermissionException - When the user does not have sufficient permissions to create/clone a project.
        CancelException - When the user has indicated that he/she wants to abort the cmd.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - When scan, model or user is a null reference.
        See Also:
        DataModel.createProject(VersionID, String, String, GregorianCalendar, Developer, long, User), DataModel.cloneProject(Project, VersionID, Developer, GregorianCalendar, long), GetProjectCmd.exec(TerminalScanner, DataModel, User)
